author: Mishaal Rahman
title: Get the Pixel Launcher from Android O on any Android 6.0.1+ Device
text: The first Android O Developer Preview was just released this week, but unless you have one of the few supported Nexus or Pixel devices you won’t be able to taste Android O for quite a long time. Nonetheless, if you’re looking to install some of the applications shipped with the Android O preview, XDA Recognized Contributor linuxct has got you covered. They’ve posted a port of the new Pixel Launcher that should work on any Android 6.0.1+ device.
